<subSubSection id="C36C2998FFD08018FF50FB5C2821F9B8" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD08018FF50FB5C2821F9B8" blockId="1.[151,1437,1266,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FF50FB5C2B2EFAE5" bold="true" box="[151,274,1266,1292]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewings with a pigmented marginal band from 
<collectionCode id="ED67E2D6FFD08018FCF9FB5C296EFAE4" box="[830,850,1266,1293]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">R</collectionCode>
4+5 to cu1 and cu2 cells (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FBAAFB5D2E92FAE4" box="[1133,1198,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Pterostigma rounded, not angulate nor extended towards Rs. Hindwings with a pigmented marginal band from 
<collectionCode id="ED67E2D6FFD08018FB10FAB82ED7FAD8" box="[1239,1259,1302,1329]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">R</collectionCode>
4+5 to cu1 and cu2 cells (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FEC9FA952B69FABC" box="[270,341,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium of three sclerites, central one large, with two median, close together, sclerotized, acuminate or distally widened posterior projections, located ventrally to a distally acuminate membranous projection (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FF15FA2D2B2BFA74" box="[210,279,1410,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Phallosome with three pairs of endophallic sclerites (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FCB9FA2D29F9FA74" box="[894,965,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs 6</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FC3BFA2D2E25FA74" box="[1020,1049,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">11</figureCitation>
), mesal endophallic sclerite fused, inverted U-shaped, with short, lateral laminar processes, postero-mesal sclerites elongate, narrow and laminar (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FAADFA092ADDFA0C" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,607,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-200@5.[151,1435,597,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Variations in the shape of the mesal endophallic sclerite of Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. 12 and 13. Pará (Brazil). 14 and 15. Valle del Cauca (Colombia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488312/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs 12–15</figureCitation>
), basally fused to lateral process, apically acuminate and connected to the external parameres. Anterior sclerites small, transverse, lateral sclerites bow-shaped, apically directed mesally and with variable processes. Species included: 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD08018FEC0F9BD286AF9C4" authority="Silva-Neto, 2021" authorityName="Silva-Neto" authorityYear="2021" box="[263,598,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FEC0F9BD2BB7F9C4" box="[263,395,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">E. atlantica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE707E2FFD08018FE54F9BD286AF9C4" author="Silva-Neto, A. M." box="[403,598,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="941" refId="ref4393" refString="Silva-Neto, A. M. (2021) A new species of Euplocania Enderlein (Psocodea, ' Psocoptera', Ptiloneuridae), from the Atlantic Rainforest, Brazil. EntomoBrasilis, 14, e 941. https: // doi. org / 10.12741 / ebrasilis. v 14. e 941" type="journal article" year="2021">Silva-Neto, 2021</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD08018FDA5F9BD2988F9C4" authority="Pereira et al., 2022" authorityName="Pereira" authorityYear="2022" box="[610,948,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macuxi">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FDA5F9BD28EFF9C5" box="[610,723,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">E. macuxi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE707E2FFD08018FD1DF9BD2988F9C4" author="Pereira, A. F. &amp; Silva-Neto, A. M. &amp; Boldrini, R." box="[730,948,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref4246" refString="Pereira, A. F., Silva-Neto, A. M. &amp; Boldrini, R. (2022) Three new species of Euplocania Enderlein (Psocodea, ' Psocoptera', Ptiloneuridae), from the state of Roraima, Brazil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 62 (e 202262010), 1 - 8. http: // doi. org / 10.11606 / 1807 - 0205 / 2022.62.010" type="journal article" year="2022">
Pereira 
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FCF6F9BD295FF9C4" box="[817,867,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">et al</emphasis>
., 2022
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD08018FC07F9BD2F54F9C4" authority="Silva-Neto et al., 2019" authorityName="Silva-Neto, Garcia Aldrete &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2019" box="[960,1384,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uariniensis">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FC07F9BD2E60F9C5" box="[960,1116,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">E. uariniensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE707E2FFD08018FBA3F9BD2F54F9C4" author="Silva-Neto, A. M. &amp; Garcia Aldrete, A. N. &amp; Rafael, J. A." box="[1124,1384,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="374 - 390" refId="ref4319" refString="Silva-Neto, A. M., Garcia Aldrete, A. N. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (2019) New species of Euplocania Enderlein (Psocodea, ' Psocoptera', Ptiloneuridae) from Brazil, with a checklist of all known species of the genus. Zootaxa, 4550 (3), 374 - 390. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4550.3.5" type="journal article" year="2019">
Silva-Neto 
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FB22F9BD2F19F9C4" box="[1253,1317,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">et al.,</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and two more species described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36C2998FFD08018FF50F90D2930F955" box="[151,780,1698,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
