</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36C2998FFD0801BFF50F9462FA1FE93" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" type="key">
<key id="FFE72D22FFD0801BFF50F9462FA1FE93" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<keyStep id="308262B6FFD08018FF50F9462FA0F8DE" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD08018FF50F9462FA1F8F3" blockId="1.[151,1437,1768,2024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD08018FF50F9462FA1F8F3" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
1. Central sclerite of the hypandrium with the two posterior median processes distally wide and curved slightly inward, each arm machete shaped (see 
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FE6AF8AB2BD9F8F2" box="[429,485,1797,1819]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4C8ED7F6FFD08018FE1EF8AB2BD9F8F2" box="[473,485,1797,1819]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" unit="in" value="6.0">6</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE707E2FFD08018FDC3F8AB2889F8F2" author="Pereira, A. F. &amp; Silva-Neto, A. M. &amp; Boldrini, R." box="[516,693,1797,1819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref4246" refString="Pereira, A. F., Silva-Neto, A. M. &amp; Boldrini, R. (2022) Three new species of Euplocania Enderlein (Psocodea, ' Psocoptera', Ptiloneuridae), from the state of Roraima, Brazil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 62 (e 202262010), 1 - 8. http: // doi. org / 10.11606 / 1807 - 0205 / 2022.62.010" type="journal article" year="2022">
Pereira 
