. 2022
</bibRefCitation>
)......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD08018FB7BF8A82FA1F8F3" authority="Pereira et al." authorityName="Pereira" box="[1212,1437,1797,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macuxi">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FB7BF8A82F20F8F2" box="[1212,1308,1798,1819]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">E. macuxi</emphasis>
Pereira 
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FAABF8A82FA1F8F3" box="[1388,1437,1797,1819]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">et al.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD08018FF50F88D2FA0F8DE" blockId="1.[151,1437,1768,2024]" box="[151,1436,1826,1848]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD08018FF50F88D2FA0F8DE" box="[151,1436,1826,1848]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
- Central sclerite of the hypandrium with the two posterior median processes distally acuminate (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FBB2F88C2E8EF8D1" box="[1141,1202,1826,1848]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs 5</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FB27F88C2EC5F8D1" box="[1248,1273,1826,1848]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">10</figureCitation>
)........... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308262B6FFD08018FF50F8EE2FA0F844" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD08018FF50F8EE2FA1F89B" blockId="1.[151,1437,1768,2024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD08018FF50F8EE2FA1F89B" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
2. Mesal endophallic sclerite with anterior margin aligned with the anterior margin of the lateral processes, appearing as a substraight anterior margin; anterior sclerites smaller than in the other three species........... 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD08018FBB4F8F02FA1F89B" authority="Silva-Neto et al." authorityName="Silva-Neto, Garcia Aldrete &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="2019" box="[1139,1437,1885,1907]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="1" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uariniensis">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FBB4F8F02EC5F89A" box="[1139,1273,1886,1907]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">E. uariniensis</emphasis>
Silva-Neto 
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FAABF8F02FA1F89B" box="[1388,1437,1885,1907]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">et al.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD08018FF50F8D52FA0F844" blockId="1.[151,1437,1768,2024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD08018FF50F8D52FA0F844" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD08018FF50F8D52AA3F879" box="[151,159,1915,1936]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">-</emphasis>
Mesal endophallic sclerite with anterior margin convex, or medially concave, lateral processes not forming a sub-straight line with the anterior margin of the sclerite (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FD98F83628A0F847" box="[607,668,1944,1966]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Figs 6</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FD0CF83628DEF847" box="[715,738,1944,1966]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">11</figureCitation>
)....................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308262B6FFD0801BFF50F81B2FA1FF23" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD08018FF50F81B2FA0F80E" blockId="1.[151,1437,1768,2024]" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD08018FF50F81B2FA0F80E" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">
3. Lateral endophallic sclerites with concave laminar process apically, clearly widened, mesal endophallic sclerite with rounded anterior margin, not concave medially (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD08018FD9BF87C289CF801" box="[604,672,2002,2024]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="130">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
)............................................................. 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD3801BFF50FF362FA1FF23" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,379]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD3801BFF50FF362FA1FF23" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
- Lateral endophallic sclerites apically with process not widened or developed as in the previous ones, mesal endophallic sclerite usually with medially concave anterior margin (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFD6AFF1B28D0FF22" box="[685,748,181,203]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,187,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1435,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. Male. 1. Forewing. 2. Hindwing. 3. Front view of head. 4. Left paraproct and epiproct. 5. Hypandrium. 6. Phallosome. (aes) anterior endophallic sclerites, (ep) external parameres, (les) lateral endophallic sclerite, (ms) mesal sclerite, (pms) postero-mesal sclerite, (st) side struts. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488301" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488301/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Figs 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFD31FF1B296AFF22" box="[758,854,181,203]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,607,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-200@5.[151,1435,597,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–15. Variations in the shape of the mesal endophallic sclerite of Euplocania guticortesorum n. sp. 12 and 13. Pará (Brazil). 14 and 15. Valle del Cauca (Colombia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488312/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">12, 14, 15</figureCitation>
)........................... 
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFB6AFF1B2FA1FF23" bold="true" box="[1197,1437,181,202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD3801BFB6AFF1B2F5CFF23" authority="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete, 2022" authorityName="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete" authorityYear="2022" box="[1197,1376,181,202]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guticortesorum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFB6AFF1B2F5CFF23" bold="true" box="[1197,1376,181,202]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">E. guticortesorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2311B7AFFD3801BFAA1FF1B2FA1FF23" box="[1382,1437,181,202]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="308262B6FFD3801BFF50FF7C2FA1FE93" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD3801BFF50FF7C2FA0FECA" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,379]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD3801BFF50FF7C2FA0FECA" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
4. Posterior processes of the central sclerite of the hypandrium distally narrow; mesal endophallic sclerite basally narrow, apical process of lateral endophallic sclerite posteriorly wide, and distally curved outward (see 
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFBF3FF412E50FEEC" box="[1076,1132,239,261]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4C8ED7F6FFD3801BFBA7FF5E2E50FEEC" box="[1120,1132,240,261]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" unit="in" value="7.0">7</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE707E2FFD3801BFB4DFF412F15FEEF" author="Silva-Neto, A. M." box="[1162,1321,239,262]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" pagination="941" refId="ref4393" refString="Silva-Neto, A. M. (2021) A new species of Euplocania Enderlein (Psocodea, ' Psocoptera', Ptiloneuridae), from the Atlantic Rainforest, Brazil. EntomoBrasilis, 14, e 941. https: // doi. org / 10.12741 / ebrasilis. v 14. e 941" type="journal article" year="2021">Silva-Neto 2021</bibRefCitation>
).......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD3801BFB79FEA32FA0FECA" authority="Silva-Neto" authorityName="Silva-Neto" box="[1214,1436,269,291]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atlantica">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFB79FEA32F12FECB" box="[1214,1326,269,290]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">E. atlantica</emphasis>
Silva-Neto
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC97A13FFD3801BFF50FE852FA1FE93" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,379]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<keyLead id="3087D926FFD3801BFF50FE852FA1FE93" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
- Posterior processes of the central sclerite of the hypandrium distally more widened than in the previous species (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFACBFE842F6FFEA9" box="[1292,1363,298,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); mesal endophallic sclerite basally broader than in the previous species, apical process of the lateral endophallic sclerites with concave laminar and crescent-shaped process (
<figureCitation id="134D6696FFD3801BFD89FECB28AEFE92" box="[590,658,357,379]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[157,1418,330,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-75@4.[151,1435,309,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Euplocania wilsoni n. sp. Male. 7. Forewing. 8. Front view of head. 9. Epiproct and right paraproct. 10. Hypandrium. 11. Phallosome. Scales in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488310" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488310/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
)................................................. 
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFB3AFECB2FA1FE93" bold="true" box="[1277,1437,356,378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">
<taxonomicName id="4C760190FFD3801BFB3AFECB2F5CFE93" authority="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete, 2022" authorityName="González-Obando &amp; Carrejo-Gironza &amp; Aldrete" authorityYear="2022" box="[1277,1376,356,378]" class="Insecta" family="Ptiloneuridae" genus="Euplocania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wilsoni" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B902A601FFD3801BFB3AFECB2F5CFE93" bold="true" box="[1277,1376,356,378]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="131">E. wilsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2311B7AFFD3801BFAA1FECB2FA1FE93" box="[1382,1437,357,378]" pageId="2" pageNumber="131" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
